#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:104
msgid "enum **Projection**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:106
msgid ""
"**PROJECTION_PERSPECTIVE** = **0** --- Perspective projection. Objects on"
" the screen becomes smaller when they are far away."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:108
msgid ""
"**PROJECTION_ORTHOGONAL** = **1** --- Orthogonal projection, also known "
"as orthographic projection. Objects remain the same size on the screen no"
" matter how far away they are."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:110
msgid ""
"**PROJECTION_FRUSTUM** = **2** --- Frustum projection. This mode allows "
"adjusting :ref:`frustum_offset <class_Camera_property_frustum_offset>` to"
" create \"tilted frustum\" effects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:120
msgid "enum **KeepAspect**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:122
msgid ""
"**KEEP_WIDTH** = **0** --- Preserves the horizontal aspect ratio; also "
"known as Vert- scaling. This is usually the best option for projects "
"running in portrait mode, as taller aspect ratios will benefit from a "
"wider vertical FOV."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:124
msgid ""
"**KEEP_HEIGHT** = **1** --- Preserves the vertical aspect ratio; also "
"known as Hor+ scaling. This is usually the best option for projects "
"running in landscape mode, as wider aspect ratios will automatically "
"benefit from a wider horizontal FOV."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:136
msgid "enum **DopplerTracking**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:138
msgid ""
"**DOPPLER_TRACKING_DISABLED** = **0** --- Disables `Doppler effect "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doppler_effect>`_ simulation (default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:140
msgid ""
"**DOPPLER_TRACKING_IDLE_STEP** = **1** --- Simulate `Doppler effect "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doppler_effect>`_ by tracking positions of"
" objects that are changed in ``_process``. Changes in the relative "
"velocity of this camera compared to those objects affect how Audio is "
"perceived (changing the Audio's ``pitch shift``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_camera.rst:142
msgid ""
"**DOPPLER_TRACKING_PHYSICS_STEP** = **2** --- Simulate `Doppler effect "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doppler_effect>`_ by tracking positions of"
" objects that are changed in ``_physics_process``. Changes in the "
"relative velocity of this camera compared to those objects affect how "
"Audio is perceived (changing the Audio's ``pitch shift``)."
msgstr ""

